A tragic shooting at a Nebraska mall left eight dead, including employees and shoppers.
The shooter, Robert A. Hawkins, had a troubled past and left a note hinting at his struggles.
The community in Omaha is coming together to support each other during this difficult time.
Hawkins had a history of legal issues, including a recent arrest for underage drinking.
The incident has shocked the nation, highlighting the ongoing issue of gun violence.
The victims' families and the community are receiving counseling to cope with the aftermath of this senseless tragedy.
